Sample parameters for PSA

Source: R/sample_params.R
sample_params.Rd

Sample parameters from their joint probability distribution for a probabilistic sensitivity analysis (PSA).

sample_params(n, params_mstate_nma = iviNSCLC::params_mstate_nma)

Arguments

n

The number of random observations of the parameters to draw.
params_mstate_nma

A list of params_surv objects, where each element in the list denotes a survival distribution. Should have the same variable names as params_mstate_nma.

Value

An object of class "sampled_params", which is a list with the following components.

mstate_nma

A params_surv object where the number of rows in each coef element is equal to n.

Examples

params <- sample_params(2)
names(params)
#> [1] "mstate_nma"

# Multi-state NMA
params$mstate_nma$weibull$coefs$shape
